<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="70" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,282,453]" pageId="14" pageNumber="70">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,280,282,308]" pageId="14" pageNumber="70">Comments</emphasis>
. This species was described based on several females collected in Fezzan (Southwestern 
<collectingCountry box="[1279,1349,282,309]" name="Libya" pageId="14" pageNumber="70">Libya</collectingCountry>
). Caporiacco indicated its size as 
<quantity box="[456,522,319,345]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="70" unit="mm" value="7.0">7 mm</quantity>
(
<quantity box="[539,605,318,345]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="70" unit="mm" value="3.0">3 mm</quantity>
carapace and 
<quantity box="[767,854,318,345]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.1" pageId="14" pageNumber="70" unit="mm" value="4.1">4.1 mm</quantity>
abdomen) in length. Judging from the shape of the epigyne given in 
<bibRefCitation author="Caporiacco, L. di" box="[350,561,354,381]" pageId="14" pageNumber="70" pagination="67 - 94" refId="ref11446" refString="Caporiacco, L. di (1936) Aracnidi fezzanesi raccolti dal Prof. G. Scortecci nel 1934 - XII (Missione della R. Societa Geografica). Atti della Societa Italiana di Scienze Naturali e del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Milano, 75, 67 - 94." type="journal article" year="1936">Caporiacco (1936)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Roewer, C. F." box="[618,804,354,381]" pageId="14" pageNumber="70" pagination="519 - 1040" refId="ref13791" refString="Roewer, C. F. (1960 a) Araneae Lycosaeformia II (Lycosidae) (Fortsetzung und Schluss). Exploration du Parc National de l'Upemba, Mission G. F. de Witte, 55, 519 - 1040." type="journal article" year="1960">Roewer (1960a)</bibRefCitation>
, it is neither 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sundevall" authorityYear="1833" box="[955,1027,355,380]" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Pirata" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="14" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[955,1027,355,380]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="70">Pirata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
nor 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", McKay" authorityYear="1979" box="[1081,1184,354,380]" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Trochosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="14" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1081,1184,354,380]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="70">Trochosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but is most similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Thorell, 1872)" baseAuthorityName="Thorell" baseAuthorityYear="1872" box="[151,529,390,416]" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Alopecosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="14" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simoni">
<emphasis box="[151,350,390,416]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="70">Alopecosa simoni</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Thorell, T." box="[365,521,390,416]" pageId="14" pageNumber="70" pagination="229 - 374" refId="ref14194" refString="Thorell, T. (1872) s. n. In: Remarks on synonyms of European spiders. Part III. C. J. Lundstro ¨ m, Uppsala, pp. 229 - 374." type="book chapter" year="1872">Thorell, 1872</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Nosek, 1905)" baseAuthorityName="Nosek" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[585,880,390,417]" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Alopecosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="14" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pentheri">
<emphasis box="[585,709,390,417]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="70">A. pentheri</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Nosek, A." box="[725,872,390,417]" pageId="14" pageNumber="70" pagination="114 - 154" refId="ref13191" refString="Nosek, A. (1905) Araneiden, Opilionen und Chernetiden. In: Penther, A. &amp; Zederbauer, E. (Eds.), Ergebnisse einer naturwissenschaftlichen Reise zum Erdschias-Dagh (Kleinasien). Annalen des Kaiserlich-Koniglichen Naturhistorischen Hofmuseums in Wien, 20, pp. 114 - 154, pls. 4 - 5." type="journal article" year="1905">Nosek, 1905</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, members of the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hahn" baseAuthorityYear="1831" box="[1075,1180,391,417]" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Alopecosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="14" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cursor">
<emphasis box="[1075,1180,391,417]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="70">A. cursor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Marusik, Y. M. &amp; Nadolny, A. A. &amp; Koponen, S." pageId="14" pageNumber="70" pagination="348 - 362" refId="ref12738" refString="Marusik, Y. M., Nadolny, A. A. &amp; Koponen, S. (2018) A survey of the Alopecosa cursor species group (Aranei: Lycosidae) from Asia. Arthropoda Selecta, 27 (4), 348 - 362. https: // doi. org / 10.15298 / arthsel. 27.4.12" type="journal article" year="2018">
Marusik 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="70">et al</emphasis>
. 2018
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Nentwig, W. &amp; Blick, T. &amp; Bosmans, R. &amp; Gloor, D. &amp; Hanggi, A. &amp; Kropf, C." box="[258,482,426,453]" pageId="14" pageNumber="70" refId="ref13121" refString="Nentwig, W., Blick, T., Bosmans, R., Gloor, D., Hanggi, A. &amp; Kropf, C. (2020) Araneae: Spiders of Europe. Version 03.2020. Available from: https: // www. araneae. nmbe. ch (accessed 17 April 2020) https: // doi. org / 10.24436 / 1" type="url" year="2020">
Nentwig 
<emphasis box="[361,410,426,452]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="70">et al</emphasis>
. 2020
</bibRefCitation>
) and because of this similarity, we transfer this species to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1885" box="[1133,1250,426,452]" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Alopecosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="14" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1133,1250,426,452]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="70">Alopecosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
